# Ecosystem platform guardrails

**North star:** NurseNest is **one** cohesive premium adaptive clinical learning ecosystem — not disconnected apps, isolated study tools, mini-products, or unrelated redesigns stitched together.

Applies to Cursor implementation, Figma-to-code handoff, AI-generated UI, and human contributors. Does **not** replace task-specific safety rules (`global-engineering-constraints`, `nursenest-production-governance`, `semantic-color-guardrails`, `truthpack-first-protocol`).

---

## 1. Platform-level ecosystem

- Converge new work toward **shared primitives**, **learner shells** (e.g. `nn-learner-page-hero`, `LearnerSurfaceCard`, `SectionContainer`, `.lv-*`), **semantic tokens**, **canonical navigation**, and **adaptive study loops**.
- **Primitive vocabulary (reuse / extend — do not duplicate):** ClinicalPanel, SignalCard, TelemetryStrip, AdaptiveRecommendationRail, StudyLoopDock, ScenarioTimeline, NGNDecisionPanel, MasteryProgressBand — anchor to existing components first (`docs/ecosystem-design-system-convergence.md`).
- Preserve **learner continuity** across lessons, practice, flashcards, CAT, dashboard, labs, ECG, and simulations — **no isolated vertical apps** or parallel IA for the same learner journeys.

## 2. Lab Values positioning

- Labs = **adaptive clinical interpretation and reasoning** integrated via **`/app/labs`** and `labs-engine` — **not** a standalone calculator, static reference sheet, or separate branded utility.
- Link into **lessons, flashcards, practice, CAT, ECG, simulations** using existing study-loop and pathway helpers.
- **Reject:** spreadsheet-first UX, separate lab branding, duplicate lab route ecosystems, disconnected scoring systems.

## 3. ECG positioning

- Core ECG learning = **integrated telemetry/clinical rhythm education** — reuse **learner shells and navigation**; premium telemetry workstation aesthetic; wired to lessons, practice, NGN, labs where clinically relevant.
- **Reject:** disconnected ECG app/sub-brand, forked telemetry UI stacks, parallel ECG-only navigation trees.

## 4. Advanced ECG product

- **Advanced ECG** is a **distinct premium product line**: **separate entitlement and upgrade architecture** from core RN/PN/NP/allied pathway subscriptions unless **product explicitly** defines bundling.
- Implementors must **avoid accidental inclusion** in default core-plan entitlement checks; keep **visual alignment** with NurseNest tokens and shells (same ecosystem identity).

## 5. Case study / simulation

- **Adaptive branching:** evolving patient states, meaningful branches, multiple endings; integrate telemetry, labs, and NGN-style judgment; reuse shared primitives and learner shells.
- **Reject:** static vignettes sold as branching, fake interactive branching, isolated simulation app chrome or nav.

## 6. Theme system (Aurora, Ocean, Garden, Midnight)

- Themes alter **accent, glow, surface tint, chart color expression, atmospheric lighting** only — **not** layout grids, spacing scale, typography scale, component hierarchy, or navigation structure.
- **Midnight:** immersive workstation / CAT density; **Ocean:** primary calm educational mode; **Garden / Aurora:** supportive / optimistic expression per palette.
- **Reject:** hardcoded colors in product UI, hot pink, muddy gradients, layout forks per theme.

## 7. Design tokens

- **Production learner/marketing product UI:** derive styling from **semantic and theme tokens** (`semantic-status-tokens.css`, `[data-theme]` / `theme-palettes.css`); extend tokens or shared CSS classes instead of raw hex, one-off shadows, arbitrary gradients, or ad-hoc spacing scales in TSX.
- See `.cursor/rules/semantic-color-guardrails.mdc` for multi-hue data/status rules.

## 8. Navigation + shell

- **One** canonical navigation and learner shell ecosystem; preserve **stable URLs**, **i18n/locale behavior**, and **server-backed entitlements**.
- **Reject:** duplicate nav systems for ECG/labs/simulations, forked learner shells that fragment the same flows.

## 9. Adaptive learning

- Reinforce **linked learning**, **adaptive recommendations**, **weak-area signals**, **continue studying**, **remediation**, and **mastery progression** using existing platform wiring — compose dashboards/study APIs; **do not** introduce parallel scoring products or disconnected “lab-only” intelligence.

## 10. Brand + typography

- Preserve **NurseNest leaf logo**, **wordmark**, **DM Sans**, optimistic premium learner emotional tone (`nursenest-production-governance.mdc`).
- **Reject:** serif body typography for product UI, enterprise-hospital gray slabs, gamer neon, generic SaaS dashboard clones, disconnected sub-brand visual languages.

## 11. Figma — mandatory premium UI process

For **aesthetic, layout, hierarchy, spacing, navigation chrome, card systems, responsiveness, or visual-design** work: **audit live UI vs the premium homepage direction**, then **create or update Figma frames** (desktop + mobile; light + dark; Ocean / Midnight / Blossom) **before** major implementation. Preserve **routing, logo, wordmark, and canonical nav** unless the product task explicitly changes them. Implementation must **match approved Figma** and converge with RN / RPN / NP / New Grad / Pre-Nursing / Allied hubs — no ad-hoc card systems or grey/neon palettes (`semantic-color-guardrails.mdc`). **Playwright** must capture desktop + mobile + theme screenshots where hub programs require it; PRs and `reports/*-FINAL.md` must list **Figma file links, frame IDs, redesigned components/routes, and side-by-side Figma vs implementation screenshots** when visuals materially change.

**Full checklist:** `docs/governance/figma-premium-ui-mandatory-process.md`.

